- Social: @cultrhealth (all platforms)

# ============================================================================
# 2. TECH STACK — DO NOT DEVIATE
# ============================================================================

Framework:       Next.js 14 App Router (NOT Pages Router)
Language:        TypeScript (strict: false, allowJs: true)
Styling:         Tailwind CSS 3.4 with @tailwindcss/typography
Fonts:           Fraunces (display), Playfair Display (headings), Inter (body)
Icons:           Lucide React (NO other icon libraries)
State:           React Context API (CreatorContext, IntakeFormContext, CartContext)
Forms:           Native React state + Zod validation (NO react-hook-form, NO formik)
Class merge:     clsx + tailwind-merge via cn() from @/lib/utils (NO CVA)
Database:        Neon PostgreSQL via @vercel/postgres SDK
Auth:            JWT via jose library (HS256)
Email:           Resend SDK
Payments:        Stripe (primary), CorePay, NOWPayments, Affirm, Klarna
Bot protection:  Cloudflare Turnstile
AI:              AI SDK v6 (@ai-sdk/openai)
Charts:          Recharts (ONLY in AnalyticsCharts.tsx and admin dashboard)
PDF:             @react-pdf/renderer
Tests:           Vitest + @testing-library/react + jsdom

DO NOT introduce: styled-components, CSS modules, emotion, MUI, Chakra, Ant Design,
Zustand, Redux, Jotai (except Daily.co dep), React Query, SWR, Prisma, Drizzle,
NextAuth, Clerk, Auth0, Supabase client, Firebase, mongoose.

# ============================================================================
# 3. HIPAA COMPLIANCE — MANDATORY
# ============================================================================

## NEVER do these:
- Log PHI (Protected Health Information) — no patient names, DOB, SSN, health
  conditions, medications, diagnoses, or treatment data in console.log/error/warn
- Log email addresses alongside health data in the same log line
- Return PHI in error responses — use generic "An error occurred" messages
- Store PHI in localStorage, sessionStorage, or cookies
- Include PHI in URL query parameters or path segments
- Send PHI to analytics (GA4, etc.) or third-party services
- Disable HTTPS or weaken TLS settings
- Remove Content-Security-Policy headers from middleware.ts

## ALWAYS do these:
- Use presigned URLs with expiration for file uploads (never direct S3)
- Return sanitized error messages to clients (no stack traces, no DB errors)
- Apply DOMPurify to all rendered markdown/HTML content
- Set `private, no-cache, no-store` headers on authenticated routes
- Use parameterized SQL queries (never string interpolation in SQL)
- Verify webhook signatures before processing any payload
- Check auth on every API route and server component that accesses patient data

## Error logging pattern:
```typescript
// CORRECT — no PHI
console.error('Order creation failed:', { orderId, errorMessage: error.message })

// WRONG — leaks PHI
console.error('Order failed for patient:', { email, medications, diagnosis })
```

# ============================================================================
# 4. FILE & NAMING CONVENTIONS
# ============================================================================

## Files:
- React components:         PascalCase.tsx      (Button.tsx, TierGate.tsx)
- Client page components:   *Client.tsx          (QuizClient.tsx, ShopClient.tsx)
- API routes:               route.ts             (Next.js App Router convention)
- Utility/lib files:        camelCase.ts         (auth.ts, db.ts, utils.ts)
- Config files:             kebab-case.ts        (product-catalog.ts, social-proof.ts)

## Functions:
- Exported async:           camelCase            (createMagicLinkToken, getMembershipTier)
- React components:         PascalCase           (Button, TierGate)
- Validators:               is*/has*/check*      (isProviderEmail, hasFeatureAccess)
- Factory/getter:           get* prefix          (getStripe, getResend)

## Variables:
- Local:                    camelCase            (normalizedEmail, sessionCookie)
- Constants:                SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (SESSION_COOKIE_NAME, TEAM_EMAILS)
- Config objects:           SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (PLANS, STRIPE_CONFIG)

## Types:
- Interfaces:               PascalCase, no I prefix  (ButtonProps, SessionPayload)
- Type aliases:             PascalCase               (PlanTier, LibraryAccess)
- Input types:              *Input suffix            (CreateWaitlistInput)
- Row/entry types:          *Entry or *Row suffix    (WaitlistEntry, SiphoxKitOrderRow)

# ============================================================================
# 5. CODE PATTERNS — FOLLOW EXACTLY
# ============================================================================

## Server/Client split:
- Pages are Server Components by default
- Interactive parts extracted to *Client.tsx files
- 'use client' MUST be the first line (before any imports) in client components
- Use next/dynamic for lazy-loading below-fold components with loading skeletons

## Import order (always):
1. React/Next.js framework   (react, next/link, next/image, next/dynamic)
2. External libraries         (stripe, resend, jose, zod)
3. Internal @/ imports        (@/lib/*, @/components/*)

## Path alias:
- Always use @/* (maps to project root)
- NEVER use relative paths like ../../lib/utils
- Defined in both tsconfig.json AND vitest.config.js

## Button component:
- ALWAYS use Button from @/components/ui/Button
- Variants: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost'
- Sizes: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'
- All variants use rounded-full
- Has isLoading prop with built-in spinner
- Uses cn() utility, NOT class-variance-authority (CVA)

## cn() utility:
```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'
className={cn('base-class', condition && 'conditional-class', className)}
```
NEVER use raw string concatenation for Tailwind classes.

## API route pattern:
```typescript
export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  try {
    const auth = await verifyAuth(request)
    if (!auth.authenticated) {
      return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 })
    }
    // ... validate input with Zod, call lib functions
    return NextResponse.json({ success: true })
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Descriptive prefix:', error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Unknown error')
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'An error occurred.' }, { status: 500 })
  }
}
```

## Auth verification — use the right function:
- Members/general:  verifyAuth(request)        from @/lib/auth
- Creators:         verifyCreatorAuth(request)  from @/lib/auth
- Admins:           verifyAdminAuth(request)    from @/lib/auth
- Providers:        verifyAuth(request) + isProviderEmail() check

## Context providers (existing — DO NOT create new state management):
- CreatorContext    — creator portal state
- IntakeFormContext — multi-step intake form state
- CartContext       — shopping cart state
- ProviderContext   — provider dashboard state

## External API wrapper pattern:
- Wrap third-party SDKs in lib/ modules
- API routes NEVER call external SDKs directly
- Lazy init pattern: `function getStripe() { return new Stripe(...) }`
- Auth headers injected internally in the wrapper
- Errors normalized to Error objects

## Return values:
- Functions return typed values or null (never undefined) for optional results
- Async functions: Promise<T | null> for fallible lookups
- JWT/Auth functions: return null on failure (never throw)
- Always use async/await (no raw Promise chains)

# ============================================================================
# 6. DATABASE RULES — @vercel/postgres
# ============================================================================

## CRITICAL: NUMERIC type coercion
@vercel/postgres returns NUMERIC columns as STRINGS. Always coerce:
```typescript
// CORRECT
const rate = Number(row.commission_rate)
const amount = parseFloat(row.tax_amount_usd)

// WRONG — silent string arithmetic bugs
const rate = row.commission_rate  // "10.00" not 10
const total = row.subtotal_usd * 1.075  // "123.45" * 1.075 = NaN or wrong
```

## SQL patterns for @vercel/postgres:
- Use make_interval(days => ${days}) for intervals (NOT CAST or INTERVAL * multiplication)
- Use IS DISTINCT FROM instead of IS NULL OR != for nullable comparisons
- Use COUNT(*)::integer to avoid NUMERIC string coercion on counts
- Use ROUND(...)::float8 for computed decimals returned to JS
- NEVER use UNION ALL with parameterized queries (duplicate param indices) — split into parallel queries and merge in JS
- NEVER use date_trunc(${variable}, ...) — use literal SQL per bucket type
- Always include GROUP BY columns in SELECT if accessed in application code

## SQL safety:
- Always use sql tagged template literals (parameterized queries)
- NEVER concatenate user input into SQL strings
- Use transactions for multi-table writes (commission + attribution)
- Add .catch() fallbacks on parallel queries so one failure doesn't crash all

## Migrations:
- Location: migrations/ directory
- Naming: NNN_description.sql (sequential numbering)
- Run manually: node scripts/run-migration.mjs
- Always add IF NOT EXISTS / IF EXISTS guards
- Never drop columns with patient data (HIPAA retention)

