# ============================================================================
# 12. TESTING RULES
# ============================================================================

## Framework: Vitest + React Testing Library
- Test files: tests/**/*.test.{ts,tsx}
- Run: npm test (or npx vitest run)
- Coverage includes: lib/**/*.ts and app/**/*.{ts,tsx}
- Environment: jsdom with @vitejs/plugin-react

## Testing patterns:
- Use @/ path alias in test imports (configured in vitest.config.js)
- Mock external services, never real API calls in unit tests
- Integration tests against staging DB use real @vercel/postgres connections
- LibraryAccess mock objects MUST include protocolBuilder field
- Test data should be isolated per run with unique prefixes, auto-cleaned in afterAll

## What NOT to test:
- Don't test internal implementation details
- Don't add tests for code you didn't change (unless fixing a bug)
- Don't create test files for unchanged code

